#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:5
msgid "Advanced Selection"
msgstr "高度な選択"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:7
msgid ""
"The select menu in edit mode contains additional tool for selecting "
"components:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:9
msgid "Mirror"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:10
msgid "Select mesh items at the mirrored location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:11
msgid "Linked :kbd:`ctrl-L`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:12
msgid "Selects all components that are connected to the current selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:13
msgid "Select Random"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:14
msgid ""
"Selects a random group of vertices, edges, or faces, based on a percentage "
"value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:15
msgid "Checker Deselect"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:16
msgid "Deselect alternating faces, to create a checker like pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:17
msgid "Select Every N Number of Vertices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:18
msgid "Selects vertices that are multiples of N."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:22
msgid "Select Sharp Edges"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:20
msgid ""
"This option will select all edges that are between two faces forming an "
"angle less than a given value, which is asked you *via* a small pop-up "
"dialog. The lower is this angle limit, the sharper will be the selected "
"edges. At ``180``, **all** \"manifold\" (see below) edges will be selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:24
msgid "Linked Flat Faces (:kbd:`Ctrl-Shift-Alt-F`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:25
msgid ""
"Select connected faces based on a threshold of the angle between them. This "
"is useful for selecting faces that are planar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:26
msgid "Select Non Manifold (:kbd:`Ctrl-Shift-Alt-M`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:27
msgid ""
"Selects vertices that are not completely bound by geometry, including border"
" edges, floating edges, and orphan vertices. Only available in Vertex and "
"Edge mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:28
msgid "Interior Faces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:29
msgid "Select faces where all edges have more than 2 faces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:30
msgid "Side of Active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:31
msgid "Selects all data on the mesh in a single axis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:32
msgid "Select Faces by Sides"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:33
msgid "Selects all faces that have a specified number of edges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:36
msgid "Loose Geometry"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:35
msgid "Select all vertices or edges that do not form part of a face."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:39
msgid "Select Similar"
msgstr "似たものを選択"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:41
#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:109
#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:147
#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:187
#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:222
#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:243
#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:278
msgid "Reference"
msgstr "リファレンス"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:49
msgid ""
"Select components that have similar attributes to the ones selected, based "
"on a threshold that can be set in tool properties after activating the tool."
" Tool options change depending on the selection mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:62
msgid "Vertex Selection Mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:54
#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:94
msgid "Normal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:55
msgid ""
"Selects all vertices that have normals pointing in similar directions to "
"those currently selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:56
msgid "Amount of Adjacent Faces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:57
msgid ""
"Selects all vertices that have the same number of faces connected to them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:58
msgid "Vertex Groups"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:59
msgid ""
"Selects all vertices in the same :doc:`vertex group "
"</modeling/meshes/vertex_groups>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:62
msgid "Amount of connecting edges"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:61
msgid ""
"Selects all vertices that have the same number of edges connected to them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:81
msgid "Edge Selection Mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:65
msgid "Length"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:66
msgid ""
"Selects all edges that have a similar length as those already selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:67
msgid "Direction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:68
msgid ""
"Selects all edges that have a similar direction (angle) as those already "
"selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:69
msgid "Amount of Faces Around an Edge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:70
msgid "Selects all edges that belong to the same number of faces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:71
msgid "Face Angles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:72
msgid ""
"Selects all edges that are between two faces forming a similar angle, as "
"with those already selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:73
msgid "Crease"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:74
msgid ""
"Selects all edges that have a similar :guilabel:`Crease` value as those "
"already selected. The :guilabel:`Crease` value is a setting used by the "
":doc:`Subsurf Modifier </modifiers/generate/subsurf>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:75
msgid "Bevel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:76
msgid ""
"Selects all edges that have the same :guilabel:`Bevel Weight` as those "
"already selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:77
msgid "Seam"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:78
msgid ""
"Selects all edges that have the same :guilabel:`Seam` state as those already"
" selected. :guilabel:`Seam` is a true/false setting used in :doc:`UV-"
"texturing </textures/mapping/uv>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:81
msgid "Sharpness"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:80
msgid ""
"Selects all edges that have the same :guilabel:`Sharp` state as those "
"already selected. :guilabel:`Sharp` is a true/false setting (a flag) used by"
" the :doc:`EdgeSplit Modifier </modifiers/generate/edge_split>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:98
msgid "Face Selection Mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:84
msgid "Material"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:85
msgid ""
"Selects all faces that use the same material as those already selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:86
msgid "Image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:87
msgid ""
"Selects all faces that use the same UV-texture as those already selected "
"(see :doc:`UV-texturing </textures/mapping/uv>` pages)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:88
msgid "Area"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:89
msgid "Selects all faces that have a similar area as those already selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:90
msgid "Polygon Sides"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:91
msgid "Selects all faces that have the same number of edges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:92
msgid "Perimeter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:93
msgid ""
"Selects all faces that have a similar perimeter as those already selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:95
msgid ""
"Selects all faces that have a similar normal as those selected. This is a "
"way to select faces that have the same orientation (angle)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:98
msgid "Co-planar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:97
msgid ""
"Selects all faces that are (nearly) in the same plane as those selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:101
msgid "Selecting Loops"
msgstr "ループを選択する"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:103
msgid "You can easily select loops of components:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:107
msgid "Edge Loops and Vertex Loops"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:117
msgid ""
"Holding :kbd:`alt` while selecting an edge selects a loop of edges that are "
"connected in a line end to end, passing through the edge under the mouse "
"pointer. Holding :kbd:`alt-shift` while clicking adds to the current "
"selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:121
msgid ""
"Edge loops can also be selected based on an existing edge selection, using "
"either :menuselection:`Select --> Edge Loop`, or the :guilabel:`Edge Loop "
"Select` option of the :guilabel:`Edge Specials` menu (:kbd:`ctrl-E`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:127
#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:203
msgid ":guilabel:`Vertex` mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:129
msgid ""
"In :guilabel:`Vertex` select mode, you can also select edge loops, by using "
"the same hotkeys, *and clicking on the edges* (not on the vertices)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:134
msgid "Longitudinal and latitudinal edge loops."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:137
msgid ""
"The left sphere shows an edge that was selected longitudinally. Notice how "
"the loop is open. This is because the algorithm hit the vertices at the "
"poles and terminated because the vertices at the pole connect to more than "
"four edges. However, the right sphere shows an edge that was selected "
"latitudinally and has formed a closed loop. This is because the algorithm "
"hit the first edge that it started with."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:145
msgid "Face Loops"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:154
msgid ""
"In face select mode, holding :kbd:`alt` while selecting an **edge** selects "
"a loop of faces that are connected in a line end to end, along their "
"opposite edges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:157
msgid ""
"In vertex select mode, the same can be accomplished by using :kbd:`ctrl-alt`"
" to select an edge, which selects the face loop implicitly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:164
msgid "Face loop selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:167
msgid ""
"This face loop was selected by clicking with :kbd:`alt-rmb` on an edge, in "
":guilabel:`face` select mode. The loop extends perpendicular from the edge "
"that was selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:174
msgid ":kbd:`alt` versus :kbd:`ctrl-alt` in vertex select mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:177
msgid ""
"A face loop can also be selected in :guilabel:`Vertex` select mode. "
"Technically :kbd:`ctrl-alt-rmb` will select an :guilabel:`Edge Ring`, "
"however in :guilabel:`Vertex` select mode, selecting an :guilabel:`Edge "
"Ring` implicitly selects a :guilabel:`Face Loop` since selecting opposite "
"edges of a face implicitly selects the entire face."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:185
msgid "Edge Ring"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:195
msgid ""
"In :guilabel:`Edge` select mode, holding :kbd:`ctrl-alt` while selecting an "
"edge selects a sequence of edges that are not connected, but on opposite "
"sides to each other continuing along a :doc:`face loop "
"</modeling/meshes/mesh_structures>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:197
msgid ""
"As with edge loops, you can also select edge rings based on current "
"selection, using either :menuselection:`Select --> Edge Ring`, or the "
":guilabel:`Edge Ring Select` option of the :guilabel:`Edge Specials` menu "
"(:kbd:`ctrl-E`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:205
msgid ""
"In :guilabel:`Vertex` select mode, you can use the same hotkeys when "
"*clicking on the edges* (not on the vertices), but this will directly select"
" the corresponding face loop..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:210
msgid "A selected edge loop, and a selected edge ring."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:213
msgid ""
"In (*A selected edge loop, and a selected edge ring*), the same edge was "
"clicked on but two different \"groups of edges\" were selected, based on the"
" different commands. One is based on edges during computation and the other "
"is based on faces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:220
msgid "Path Selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:233
msgid "Select a face or vertex path with :kbd:`ctrl-rmb`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:236
msgid ""
"Selects all geometry along the shortest path from the active "
"vertex/edge/face to the one which was selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:241
msgid "Loop Inner-Region"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:251
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Select Loop Inner-Region` selects all edges that are inside a "
"closed loop of edges. While it is possible to use this operator in  "
":guilabel:`Vertex` and :guilabel:`Face` selection modes, results may be "
"unexpected. Note that if the selected loop of edges is not closed, then all "
"connected edges on the mesh will be considered inside the loop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:258
msgid "Loop to Region."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:265
msgid "This tool handles multiple loops fine, as you can see."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:272
msgid "This tool handles \"holes\" just fine as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:276
msgid "Boundary Loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:286
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Select Boundary Loop` is the \"logical inverse\" of "
":guilabel:`Select Loop Inner-Region`, based on all regions currently "
"selected, it selects only the edges at the border of these regions. It can "
"operate in any select mode, but will always switch to :guilabel:`Edge` "
"select mode when run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:288
msgid "All this is much more simple to illustrates with examples:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/selecting/advanced.rst:295
msgid ""
"Select Boundary Loop does the opposite and forces into Edge Select Mode"
msgstr ""
